content.text:
The Timestamp Change Event (refer to Figure 236) contains the current timestamp, reported in the event
header, and the timestamp from the time at which the timestamp was changed (i.e., the old timestamp).
The Timestamp Change Event shall set the Persistent Event Log Event Header:
•
Event Type field to 03h; and
•
Event Type Revision field to 01h.
The Timestamp Change Event data is specified in Figure 236.

tables.title: Table_5_2_12_1_14_2_3_Timestamp_Change_Event_Event_Type_03h
tables.table_md:
| Bytes | Description |
|:---|:---|
| 07:00 | Previous Timestamp (PTSP): Contains a timestamp of the time immediately before the timestamp was changed (i.e., the old timestamp) using the Timestamp data structure as defined in Figure 414. |
| 15:08 | Milliseconds Since Reset (MSR): Contains the time since the last Controller Level Reset reported in milliseconds. |
